comment: Sorry that I can't even collect myself enough to type in Ukrainian.  It has been over two months since I've seen my home/birth country invaded, bombed, tried to be destroyed.  My father and his parents are still in Kyiv.  I have extended family and family friends all over Ukraine and Eastern Europe.  Every day my heart breaks that my beloved Ukraine is undergoing this assault.  I wish the war to be over, but until it is, I am proud to call myself Ukrainian (though I have been in the US most of my life at this point) and see how our people will not go down and will fight for our fellow Ukrainians and our Ukraine.  I pray for everyone in Ukraine and every Ukrainian across the world who is living through this nightmare.  Glory to Ukraine!  Glory to our heroes! <3
